Every year we have students come visit us on a "Walking Tour" for a field trip where they learn about how businesses work. Due to Covid-19 our 3rd grade class couldn't visit this year. So we sent them a Virtual Walking Tour of our office. Enjoy!
**There are 2 pop quizzes in the video, hope you get the answers right!
::Also while watching you will see our famous bank vault that everyone loves to see when they visit- Guess the year and the amount we paid for this building::

Hey Kindergarten Class of 2033 we are looking for you! The process is a bit different this year due to the Stay at Home order.
First step: If you’re a parent to an upcoming K student please go to
Swanton-oh.finalforms.com and register for the 2020-2021 school year.

Next step: scan all documents (birth certificate, immunization records, proof of residency - a full utility bill, and any court or custody paperwork if there are any, to Kregistration@swantonschools.org.
::If the documents scanned are not legible you will be contacted on May 14/15th. All documents are due by May 15, 2020::

post_text:
Attention parents of high school students! The SHS teachers have been posting assignments online since last week. Your students all have work that they should be doing. You can see what has been assigned by using this link https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1lYa9I_15kUu0m7IfEinhxlAOoysmkw-uZygwta5qwyU/edit#gid=1085438863

It is very important that high school students continue to complete assignments and participate in their online classes. They are still working to earn credits toward graduation. Any classes not passed during this time will need to be made up in credit recovery next year. Don't let that happen! Keep up with your work and stay on track to graduate on time! This is especially true for the Class of 2020. If you expect to graduate and earn a diploma this year you still have one quarter left to complete. You can do it! Go Bulldogs!

post_text: In order to comply with Governor DeWine's "stay at home" order the Swanton Local School District Board Office will be closed to the public starting tomorrow 3/24/20. This will also apply to our school buildings. We will continue to respond to email and to voicemails. Should a community member need something from the board office we will schedule a time for that to happen. You can contact the superintendent's secretary at becky.nelson@swantonschools.org or leave a voicemail at 419-826-7085. Thank you all for your flexibility during these unprecedented times. Stay safe.

The following message is from our food service director regarding free meals for students:

FOOD SERVICES UPDATE

Swanton Local School District will serve meals from three locations starting 3/16/2020:

Swanton Public Library Parking Lot at: 305 Chestnut St, Swanton, OH 43558

The front entrance of Arrowhead Lake at: 2170 S Berkey Southern Rd, Swanton, OH 43558

The Mail Pouch Saloon at: 14260 Airport Hwy, Swanton, OH 43558
Meals will be available at Swanton Public Library parking lot and Arrowhead Lake from 8:30am to 9:30am and 11.30-12.30 for any child under the age of 18. At the Mail Pouch Saloon, meals will be served from 11:30am to 12:30pm, we will provide a cold healthy meal for lunch as well as provide a breakfast for the following day to each child that comes to the Mail Pouch Saloon.
Those meals will be provided only to children who show up in person. No adult meals will be available at this time.

Christian Martinez
Director of Dining Services
Swanton Local School District
christian.martiinez@swantonschools.org
419-205-4950

Meals will be available at Swanton Public Library parking lot and Arrowhead Lake from 8:30am to 9:30am and 11.30-12.30 for any child under the age of 18. At the Mail Pouch Saloon, meals will be served from 11:30am to 12:30pm, we will provide a cold healthy meal for lunch as well as provide a breakfast for the following day to each child that comes to the Mail Pouch Saloon.
Those meals will be provided only to children who show up in person. No adult meals will be available at this time.

Christian Martinez
Director of Dining Services
Swanton Local School District

post_text: The 2020 Census is just around the corner. Make sure you’re counted! An accurate snapshot means communities across the nation, including Swanton, receive the funding, services, and business support they deserve and need. For the first time, you can respond to the census online. Please be on the lookout for postcards, from the US Census Bureau, with more information coming your way beginning March 12. Please help us spread the word by SHARING this post. #2020Census
